snippet.textDisplay:
In regards to doing better with self love, it is really easy to base your self esteem off of achievements or your actions. However, we need to view our own value off of things that we are not what we do. Every day it is a great self love exercise to just tell yourself the things that you love about who you are. I am kind, I am intelligent, I am perceptive, etc. Even things such as I am a good friend, I am good at making youtube videos, I am good at making people smile, I am good at sewing, I am great at making crafty shit etc. can be limited in promoting a genuine self love because if you focus on things that you do rather than what you are and circumstances change like - you make a mistake with a friendship or say you make a video that doesn't get as many views as you want, or one day you just can't seem to make the people around you as happy as you usually do then it can lead to an anger at oneself or a resentment. Or what if - God forbid- something terrible happened and you were paralyzed from the neck down and you were no longer able to sew, to make cool ass apartment makeovers yourself, to stand upright to show your outfits on your fashion videos. Would your worth change? How would you feel about yourself? Looking on the outside in - would you think that someone else's worth would be less than if they were paralyzed? No. Because worth is not based on what we do it is based on what we are.


Here is what I have observed. You are very humble, you are crazy intelligent, you are creative beyond compare, and your value is and has been constant your entire life regardless of actions, how anyone has ever made you feel about yourself, what you achieve, what standards you do/ do not feel you meet in regards to social standards, etc. Your value is based on your being. The idea of equality and value of each human being needs to be applied to yourself as well as others. Remember to remind yourself of these things. Happy New Year. Good luck!


P.S. There is this self love podcast I really like on Spotify called The Self Love Fix by lillypad1576 that has really helped me out.
